      "role": "user",
      "content": "The Neutral-Score framework focuses on removing proxy variables that correlate too closely with protected classes like race or ethnicity. It's meant to be more equitable. Basically, we want to stop the system from making assumptions based on zip codes or other demographic-adjacent data points that have been skewing our risk profiles. As for evaluation, we'll just be looking at whether the new model's default rates are within the expected range compared to the old ones.",
